author: Inside Edition
description: Folks can't stop talking about Sydney Sweeney's eye-popping sheer dress that left little to the imagination. Megyn Kelly lashed out at the actress, giving the look a thumbs down. Kelly says she can't understand why Sweeney would want to wear a gown like that, noting, "I object to this. I disapprove of the dress she wore." But Jenna Bush Hager came to Sweeney's defense with three words: "She looked gorgeous."
title: Sydney Sweeney's Sheer Dress Has Eyes Popping And Some Fingers Wagging

author: Inside Edition
description: Yesterday, he was Prince Andrew. Today, he woke up a commoner, named Mr. Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor. The younger brother to King Charles III was stripped of his royal titles and honors. Andrew's ex-wife also loses her title, and is now simply named Sarah Ferguson. The family of Virginia Giuffre, who claims she was paid to have sex with Andrew when she was still a minor, is speaking out, calling her "a normal girl who has taken down a prince."
title: Prince Andrew Now Just Plain Mr. Mountbatten-Windsor

author: Inside Edition
description: Model and TV personality Heidi Klum struggled to stay on her feet as ferocious winds lashed the observation deck of the Empire State Building. The episode began as Heidi posed for photographers indoors, for the lighting of the iconic building's Halloween display. Then the photo session moved outdoors, where Klum was clobbered by Mother Nature eighty-six stories above street level. She gave it her best shot, but knew when to quit.
title: Heidi Klum Battles Umbrella

author: Inside Edition
description: Halloween took over television, as on-air hosts got into the holiday spirit with their costumes. "Today" co-host Craig Melvin dressed up as Prince, and even sang "Purple Rain" for Inside Edition. Savannah Guthrie went as Meryl Streep in "The Devil Wears Prada," and Jenna Bush Hager went as the woman who inspired the character: legendary Vogue editor Anna Wintour. Over at "Live With Kelly and Mark" they kicked off the show as life-sized Labubus!
title: TV Hosts Channel Prince, Beyonce, Anna Wintour For Halloween

author: Inside Edition
description: Never afraid to push the envelope, Julia Fox is known for her daring outfit choices. But some commenters think Julia Fox may have gone too far with her Halloween costume this year. Dressed as the late Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis, Fox wore a vintage-style pink suit, similar to one favored by the former first lady. But a closer look at Fox's costume reveals a red splatter on the front. The fake blood is a Halloween-inspired nod to John F. Kennedy's 1963 assassination.
title: Did Julia Fox Go Too Far With Bloody Jackie O. Halloween Costume?

author: Inside Edition
description: We hope you enjoy the 🍬TREAT🍬 at the end of every episode as much as Eva does! Happy Halloween from the Inside Edition team!
title: Eva Leaves A Treat At The End Of Every Inside Edition Episode! #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: An influencer in the world of trucking has suddenly died. Oti Cabadas, who went by Coco Trucker Girl on Instagram, passed away, according to the Spanish Federation of Freight Transport. The organization says she opened doors for many women in her profession, proving that it's not just a man's job. She documented her travels and trucking adventures on social media, opening up the industry to viewers around the world with passion and enthusiasm. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Spanish Trucking Influencer Oti Cabadas Dies Of Stroke At 41

author: Inside Edition
description: A horrific case, cold for over 60 years, finally has closure. Carol Ann Dougherty was 9 years old when she was found dead in the choir loft of a church in Pennsylvania in October of 1962. This week, the District Attorney says they can finally name her killer: William Schrader. The prosecutor's office presented all of their findings to the Bucks County Investigative Grand Jury, who found him guilty of the rape and murder of Carol Ann. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 1962 Cold Case Killing Of 9-Year-Old Carol Ann Dougherty Solved

author: Inside Edition
description: Holly Hill ordered a margarita at a Mexican restaurant near her home in Oklahoma. After one sip, she ran to the bathroom and called her mom saying she needed to go to the emergency room.
title: Margarita Mixed With Oven Cleaner Led To Woman's Death, Says Family #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: It took more than 100 years for these messages to be delivered. An Australian family found this bottle during a beach clean up. They could see the letters inside and took great care opening it up. They were written in 1916 by two soldiers on their way to France to fight in World War I. The family was able to track down the soldiers' descendants and let them know what they found. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Letters From WWI Soldiers Found In Bottle Washed Up On Beach In Australia
